race.comment: The big one of the day, which presents PITTSBURGH PIRATE (1) with a prime opportunity to run another big race in a country feature. Horsham Cup winner three back who was runner-up in the Mortlake Cup the start after before a great second at Flemington during Cup Week. Only narrowly beaten that day under the same weight he has here, so the 60kg won't be an issue. SHULTZY (6) turned in a decent effort last start to finish third over 2006m at Kyneton. Won't find this as tough so he is all set to build on that latest effort providing he leaves the gates well, which he's been doing better of late. MIRACLE SPIN (5) hasn't been able to break through for an extended period, the latest effort an eighth over 1800m at Morphettville. Fitter now, though. So too SHAHZAD (3), who was beaten 8 lengths into eighth at the second run back from a break over 2200m at Ararat two weeks ago. CRAFTY BOSS (2) was only fair at Dunkeld last week but gets to 2000m and he has a good record at that trip.
